title: For Sale:  Sites Spectre 9mm
postcontent:
9mm Sites Spectre imported by North American Arms 
Includes: One 30rd mag and two 50rd mags, Pelican case, single point harness and mag loading tool.

Must have FOID Card and person to person only.

The Spectre SMG was developed by Italian company SITES in the mid-1980s. Spectre was designed primarily for close combat, anti-terror or police operations thatrequire compact size, instant firepower at the short ranges and safety of operations.

Spectre is a recoil operated, automatic firearm. It fires from the closed bolt, an is a hammer-fired. The trigger group is more similar to handguns, than to SMG - it is Double Action without manual safety but with decocker. So, Spectre could be carried with loaded chamber and hammer down and then fired immediately simply by pressing the trigger. The receiver of the Spectre is made from stamped steel. The bolt is so designed that it acts as an air pump to push air through barrel shroud and provide additional cooling for the barrel and action (very useful when firing long bursts). Spectre has top-folding stock and polymer forward handle. It uses high-capacity, four column magazines for increased firepower.

postcontent:
Effective And Trusted Performance With Something Special.  Pistol is in factory new condition, only 40 rounds fired through it.  Family emergency forces sale, asking $875.00 or best offer, cash only please no trades.  Will ship to your nearest FFL Dealer anywhere in the USA as long as this pistol is legal to own in your state. 

The PX4 Storm Special Duty was developed to meet the very demanding requirements of the original .45 caliber JCP (Joint Combat Pistol) specifications issued by SOCOM: superior weather resistance, three magazines (one 9-round flush and two 10-round extended), dark earth frame, extended barrel, tactical case and additional accessories.
Developed For JCP Program According To SOCOM Specs.

Rotating Barrel:
The Px4’s unique rotating barrel and locking system dissipates recoil energy radially, reducing felt recoil and muzzle raise.

Ambidextrous Safety:
The ambidextrous safety lever is easily accessible by the thumb of a right or left handed shooter. The safety lever also functions as the pistol’s decocking lever. 

Accessory Rail:
The frame of the PX4 Storm has an integral Picatinny MILSTD-1913 rail for rapid attachment of tactical lights and laser aiming devices.

Automatic Firing Pin Block:
The front part of the firing pin is blocked from any forward movement until the trigger is pulled completely back. Since the block is visible, the user may ascertain its proper operation at any time.

External Hammer Design:
A traditional feature of Beretta pistols, this design provides the most energy to the firing pin, virtually eliminating the possibility of misfires due to light primer strikes. Also provides an immediate visual and tactile indicator as to the cocked/ uncocked status of the pistol. Hammer unit can be easily removed.

Individual Side Grips:
Pistol may be configured with small, medium or large back-straps to individually fit the hand of each shooter. The back-straps are checkered to ensure a firm grip in both wet or dry shooting conditions.

Reversible Magazine Release:
Multiple-sized, reversible magazine release buttons allow for customization to the individual’s hand size. Small size comes standard on the gun, while medium and large buttons are available as accessories and easy replacement. Each size may be positioned for right-handed or left-handed use.

title: For Sale:   .50 AE Desert Eagle - Gold Titanium Nitrite Tiger Stripe
postcontent:
The Magnum Research Desert Eagle is a semi-automatic large-frame pistol chambered in .50 AE. Desert Eagles don’t have a typical pistol design instead it uses a gas-operated rotating bolt, which is a trait more common for rifles. It has a fixed barrel and front end, so the bolt blows back instead of a slide. Features include an ambidextrous safety and when engaged it disables the trigger and blocks the firing pin, so even if it drops it won’t discharge. Magnum Research's founders, Jim Skildum and John Risdall had been involved with the company since 1979. Both men oversaw the ascent of the Desert Eagle® Pistol from a concept on paper to a pop culture icon including a Playboy magazine front cover featuring Pamela Anderson showing off a Pink Desert Eagle pistol. Since 2009 the Desert Eagle Pistol has been produced in the USA at MRI's Pillager, MN facility. The Desert Eagle pistols are made in a number of distinctive and appealing finishes including classic brushed chrome and the latest the distinctive and collectable “Tiger Stripe” pattern - a Gold Titanium Nitride - Authentic Bengal Tiger Striped coated finish, which is a very hard surface. The DE is very easy to disassemble for cleaning. Warranty papers are in each box, including safety cable and Bolt tool. This gun includes an extra MR magazine [7 rounds] and 20 boxes [20 rds ea.] - 400 total rounds of factory 300 -325 Gr. ammo. Gun(s) and the ammo are very hard to find on the open market, NIB [New in the box], as these are. This gun has the fancy hand inlaid engraved grips [Silver, Brass and Gold], as seen in the pictures. They are an extra $325.00 ea. [my cost from < www.Handmadegrips.com > in Istanbul, Turkey]  See Pictures here > http://goo.gl/UvI3ru

THIS SALE IS FOR CASH ONLY - $100.00 BILLS

You must have South Carolina CWP "OR" an FFL. Sale must be for pickup near my location with signed and witnessed copies of MY bill of sale. You must be a qualified buyer under South Carolina State Law.

Desert Eagle Technical Data
General Features

The Picatinny rail located on the barrel runs from the chamber area to right behind the front sight allowing the use of scope rings (optional) and aftermarket optics.

The Desert Eagle Pistol is a gas-operated, semi-automatic pistol with a rotating three lug bolt for positive lock-up.
The barrel is locked in place, assuring a high degree of accuracy.
The polygonal rifling reduces barrel wear, is easy to clean and very accurate.
Anatomically formed grip, ideal hand seating angle and comfortable grip dimensions permit rapid, accurate, instinctive shooting. The Desert Eagle is designed for two-handed shooting.
The Desert Eagle Pistol fires standard factory ammunition.
The Desert Eagle Pistol has an automatic slide lock that holds the slide open after the last round is fired.

title: Want To Buy:  WWII Weapons, Relics and Personal Accounts (Strictly for Educational Purposes)
postcontent:
I am interested in purchasing any and all WWII Era weapons and relics from any country during that period.  This includes but not limited to:
Rifles, clips, magazines
Handguns, magazines
Knives/Swords/Bayonets/Blades
Flags
Uniforms/Brass/Emblems/Medals/Patches/Belts
Photographs/Film/Maps/Drawings & First Hand Accounts (Copies are fine)
Dead Grenades, Artillery Shells, mines
Tents, packs, pouches, canteens, tools etc.

Anything acquired is for personal and educational purposes only.  Nothing acquired will be resold or used for commercial or monetary gain.  My grandfather served in Europe, landing initially in North Africa (Torch), to Sicily, onto D-Day at Anzio, eventually up through Italy, into France and on to Germany.  After his recent passing, I am following his personal account and experience of the war to re-create a living collection of what he may have used, encountered, seen or come by.  

Anyone with whom I meet that is interested, whether or not we exchange anything, I will be happy to provide you with a copy of my grandfather's account of the war.

Unfortunately, the Greatest Generation is aging and regrettably we will see those who preserved the world's freedom pass on into history.  Text books can provide a 'bigger picture' view of the events that took place; however it is often through the personal accounts of those who witnessed these events first hand that can truly provide the best insight into the daily conditions and emotions the men and women who served experienced.  My goal is to collect and organize as much information on this critically important period of history as I can so that I may share it with others and preserve the experiences of those who were there.

Not much to say, its not pretty, but if you know these actions, you know they work! Then, now, and after.

The action is extremely slick, trigger has some loose play, but tightens up crisp light and consistant. 

The bad: obviously it has a sporter stock, no lug, sport mag, and a folding rear sight replacing the peep. Also there is significant blueing loss but little to no pitting or rust. 
(where it looks like pitting on the barrel it isn't! Its some of the remaining blueing against the metallic wear.
The stock has a couple nicks but nothing to make it non functional.

The good: Slick action, good trigger for a mil-surp, strong rifling, strong, solid action. 
And there is a nice pad on the the stock so recoil is mild at best.

Will sell, or trade!  Having trouble uploading pics, but I have them and will gladly send.

You have to get the light just right to see them and they would very easily buff out with a Scotch-Brite pad, as they don't go into the metal. They are just on the surface finishing.
